1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,469
Thank you so much.

2
00:00:00,469 --> 00:00:09,429
I gave SpaceX less than a 10% chance of succeeding at all

3
00:00:09,429 --> 00:00:10,710
to be clear.

4
00:00:10,710 --> 00:00:11,950
In fact, I told people this.

5
00:00:11,950 --> 00:00:13,450
Look, we're probably going to fail,

6
00:00:13,450 --> 00:00:17,469
but we should give it a try because if we don't,

7
00:00:17,469 --> 00:00:20,350
if there's not a new company that enters space,

8
00:00:20,350 --> 00:00:25,030
we will never be a truly space-bearing civilization.

9
00:00:25,030 --> 00:00:27,509
And while the other aerospace companies,

10
00:00:27,509 --> 00:00:29,549
they build good rockets and everything,

11
00:00:29,549 --> 00:00:32,509
they were simply not pursuing the technology that's necessary

12
00:00:32,509 --> 00:00:40,230
to make life multi-planetary, to make Star Trek,

13
00:00:40,230 --> 00:00:44,590
to make the exciting science fiction

14
00:00:44,590 --> 00:00:47,750
futures that we've read about real.

15
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:50,069
And that's what SpaceX is all about,

16
00:00:50,069 --> 00:00:53,310
is to take the fiction out of science fiction

17
00:00:53,310 --> 00:00:59,370
and create an exciting, inspiring future for everyone.

18
00:00:59,370 --> 00:01:01,170
SpaceX wants to be able to take you to the moon,

19
00:01:01,170 --> 00:01:05,290
take you to Mars, and ultimately beyond.

20
00:01:05,290 --> 00:01:12,569
And I'm confident at this point that with the incredible team

21
00:01:12,569 --> 00:01:27,459
that we have here at SpaceX, that we will do that for you.

22
00:01:27,459 --> 00:01:28,859
There are always problems on Earth.

23
00:01:28,859 --> 00:01:30,060
There are always problems on Earth.

24
00:01:30,060 --> 00:01:32,579
There are always things that we wish to be better,

25
00:01:32,579 --> 00:01:33,980
that we want to solve here on Earth.

26
00:01:33,980 --> 00:01:35,819
And we should solve them.

27
00:01:35,819 --> 00:01:38,180
But there also have to be things that

28
00:01:38,180 --> 00:01:40,900
get you excited about the future,

29
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:44,180
that make you glad to wake up in the morning,

30
00:01:44,180 --> 00:01:47,819
because you can't wait to see what happens next.

31
00:01:47,819 --> 00:01:48,000
And that's the future that SpaceX wants to bring to you.
